<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,463,488]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Etymology.</emphasis>
A composed Latin noun (nigri + genu), meaning “black-knee”, in reference to the dark markings on the middle portion of the legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The embolic disc and embolus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[743,888,531,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[743,888,531,555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[900,995,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[900,995,530,555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1284,1393,530,555]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[1284,1393,530,555]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" box="[269,446,566,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis box="[269,446,566,591]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[507,626,566,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[507,626,566,591]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[636,729,566,591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[636,729,566,591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: there are two dPED and the vPED is proximal and projects retrolaterally; also, the embolus is thicker and sickle-shaped in these species (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1101,602,627]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C). However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1256,1396,603,627]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1256,1396,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the short and rounded RvTA with two teeth on the border (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1241,638,663]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
D), being slender and sinuous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[324,429,674,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[324,429,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" box="[487,662,674,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis box="[487,662,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, short with one tooth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[945,1079,675,699]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis box="[945,1079,675,699]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano" box="[1141,1298,674,699]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1967) Dos nuevas especies del genero Amphidraus Simon, 1900 (Araneae, Salticidae). Physis Buenos Aires (C), 27, 95 - 100." type="journal article" year="1967">Galiano 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4), and finger-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[340,457,710,735]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[340,457,710,735]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[463,553,710,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,553,710,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[568,643,710,735]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig 14</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,713,746,771]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus box="[418,521,746,771]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode box="[535,621,746,771]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">MPEG</collectionCode>
32688).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.93. Carapace 1.44 long, 1.03 wide and 0.80 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.57 long. Anterior eye row 1.10 wide, posterior 0.91 wide. Legs: 3412. Length of leg I 2.20 (0.72 + 0.76 + 0.72); II 2.16 (0.72 + 0.76 + 0.68); III 2.96 (0.95 + 0.95 + 1.06); IV 2.92 (0.87 + 0.95 + 1.10). Palp (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,846,871]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Figs 12</figureCitation>
A–D): femur with subproximal ventral projection (
<figureCitation box="[811,896,846,871]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Figs 12</figureCitation>
A, 12D); tibia with reduced RTA and depression below the apophyses (
<figureCitation box="[401,487,879,904]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Figs 12</figureCitation>
B, 12D); embolic filament longer than straight, sclerotized portion (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1331,879,904]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
C). Color in alcohol: thoracic area brown and cephalic area black; abdomen dorsally almost black; ventrally pale; legs with dark spots (
<figureCitation box="[280,363,946,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="13.[151,250,2011,2033]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1203,1974]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,1203,1974]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 11. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A male Holotype, dorsal view; B same, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855467/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Figs 11</figureCitation>
A, 11B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" box="[199,418,980,1005]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,980,1005]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" box="[199,1017,1013,1038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1013,1038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[608,656,1014,1038]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">type</typeStatus>
locality (
<collectingCountry box="[762,835,1013,1038]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[846,898,1014,1038]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Pará</collectingRegion>
) (
<figureCitation box="[920,1004,1013,1038]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[210,1378,193,1011]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[210,1378,193,1011]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 31. Map of records of A. bifidus sp. nov., A. nigrigenu sp. nov. and A. draconicaudatus sp. nov. For context of tHis map witHin SoutH America, see Fig. 28." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855541/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,397,1138]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1046,1071]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Note.</emphasis>
Although we have found large variation in male palp structure of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1016,1149,1047,1070]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis box="[1016,1149,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which could include the palp of the 
